# Builder CLI layout rules

When you touch **CLI surface** (`bin/aifabrix.js`, `lib/cli.js`, `lib/cli/**`, `lib/commands/**`) or **shared CLI formatters**, you must keep behavior aligned with the canonical docs in this folder.

## Sources of truth (read before shipping)

| Document | Role |
| -------- | ---- |
| [layout.md](./layout.md) | Visual and semantic spec: colors, sections, glyphs, blocking vs warning, non-TTY/CI, helper map to `cli-test-layout-chalk.js`. |
| [cli-output-command-matrix.md](./cli-output-command-matrix.md) | **One row per leaf command**: expected **output profile** (layout-blocks, tty-summary, stream-logs, json-opt, stdout-only, delegate). |

If implementation and `layout.md` disagree, **fix implementation** or **update docs** in the same change so they stay one story.

## Output profiles (from the matrix)

Use the matrix row for your command to decide UX:

- **layout-blocks** — Structured blocks (header, verdict, lists, failures). Prefer helpers from `lib/utils/cli-test-layout-chalk.js` (or `lib/utils/cli-layout-chalk.js` re-export). Respect **`--json`**: skip TTY-only layout when the command is classified **json-opt** or when JSON mode is documented for that flow.
- **tty-summary** — Short chalk lines / tables; still use canonical glyphs and semantic colors.
- **stream-logs** — Tail/stream style; do not force layout-blocks around raw log lines unless product asks for a wrapper.
- **json-opt** — Human TTY layout when interactive; **machine-oriented** output when `--json` (no decorative layout).
- **stdout-only** — Stable, script-friendly stdout; minimal chalk; often used for diffs or piping.
- **delegate** — Output comes from delegated library (wizard, etc.); still avoid forbidden glyphs and spurious decoration in anything you add.

**New leaf command:** add a row to [cli-output-command-matrix.md](./cli-output-command-matrix.md) with the correct profile combination.

## Glyphs and semantics (terminal only)

From [layout.md](./layout.md) contributor appendix:

| Role | Use | Do not use |
| ---- | --- | ----------- |
| Success | **✔** | ✓, heavy check, decorative check emoji |
| Warning | **⚠** | ‼, random emoji |
| Failure | **✖** | ✗, `x`, decorative X |
| Skipped | **⏭** | — |
| In progress | **⏳** | Hourglass as pure decoration |

- **Red = blocking only** (hard failure / non-zero exit when that line is the verdict). **Yellow = non-blocking** warnings. Never use red for warnings.
- **Non-TTY / CI** (`NO_COLOR`, chalk level 0): **same glyphs and line structure**; colors become no-ops. Do not invent a second plain-text vocabulary (e.g. `[OK]` instead of ✔) unless the command is explicitly **stdout-only machine** output.

Markdown headings in `layout.md` may use emoji for doc navigation; **user-facing terminal strings** follow the semantic glyph table only.

## Implementation

- **Canonical helpers:** `lib/utils/cli-test-layout-chalk.js` (see symbol → helper table in [layout.md](./layout.md) § “Implementation map”).
- **Preferred import alias:** `lib/utils/cli-layout-chalk.js` re-exports the same API when the path should not contain `test`.
- **Prefer** `formatSuccessLine`, `formatSuccessParagraph`, `formatBlockingError`, `failureGlyph`, `successGlyph`, and other exported section helpers over ad hoc `` chalk.green(`✔ …`) `` for one-off success/error lines.
- **Composite / indented lines** (e.g. `successGlyph()` + `chalk.white(…)`, or `  ✔ …` in validate-style output) may stay raw chalk **only** when a single helper would not match the spec; keep glyphs canonical.
- **Tests:** extend or add tests under `tests/lib/utils/cli-test-layout-chalk.test.js` (and command tests) when behavior or snapshots encode layout.

## Code entry points and maintenance

- **Shared formatters:** `lib/utils/cli-test-layout-chalk.js` (canonical exports).
- **Neutral re-export:** `lib/utils/cli-layout-chalk.js` → same module.
- **Unit tests:** `tests/lib/utils/cli-test-layout-chalk.test.js`.

**Optional follow-up:** If you touch centralized command error handling (e.g. `handleCommandError`), consider aligning it with `formatBlockingError` (but preserve `--json` / stdout-only behavior for script modes).

## Commander and UX checklist

- [ ] **Help**: `.description()` and `.option()` texts clear; default values and env overrides documented when behavior is non-obvious.
- [ ] **Profile**: Matrix row added/updated for every new **leaf** command path.
- [ ] **JSON / script**: If the command supports `--json` or machine output, JSON path skips TTY layout and stays stable for scripts.
- [ ] **Errors**: Blocking failures use **✖** + red via shared helpers where possible; non-blocking issues use **⚠** + yellow.
- [ ] **Docs**: User-facing CLI documentation lives under `docs/` per [docs-rules.mdc](./docs-rules.mdc) (command-centric; no raw HTTP/API tutorial in user docs unless that doc is explicitly contributor-focused).

